        "content": "<p>You also need 2 to be invertible (which holds in your case).</p>",
        "id": 455120966,
        "sender_full_name": "Scott Carnahan",
        "timestamp": 1722345428
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>If you already know that the extension is galois then <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=exists_root_adjoin_eq_top_of_isCyclic#doc\">docs#exists_root_adjoin_eq_top_of_isCyclic</a> works.<br>\nIf not then <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Field.powerBasisOfFiniteOfSeparable#doc\">docs#Field.powerBasisOfFiniteOfSeparable</a> gives a generator with a deg 2 monic minimal polynomial and you can just shift the generator. We don't have this in mathlib IIRC and it would be nice to have.</p>",
        "id": 455151038,
        "sender_full_name": "Andrew Yang",
        "timestamp": 1722353373
    },
